results.name: Numbers n with more prime factors (counted with multiplicity) than n+1.
comment: First differs from A074827 in having 104.
example: 104 has four prime factors (2, 2, 2, 13), while 105 has only three (3, 5, 7), so 104 belongs to the sequence.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Dec 28 2018
